text: Lebesby or Davvesiidda gielda, is a municipality in Norway's northernmost county, Finnmark. The settlements include Lebesby (settlement). ==Administration== The municipal council is elected until late 2027. *10 council members are from the Labour partyhttps://www.nrk.no/valg/2023/resultat/fylke/56/5624. NRK.no. Retrieved 2023-09-26 *3 from Conservative party *2 from Centre party *2 from Socialist Left party (17 council members were elected during the 2023 Norwegian local elections.) ==Related pages== *List of mayors in Norway that are elected until 2027 ==References== Category:Municipalities of Finnmark
